# Template — requirements & agent guidelines

**This repo is a starter template, not a finished product.** Before launch, the user must replace placeholder copy, branding, env vars, API URLs, metadata, and assets. Do not treat placeholder names (`YourApp`, `App`, template metrics) as production values.

See also: `template-context.mdc` (structure), `docs/COMPONENTS.md`, `docs/LANDING.md`, `docs/FONTS.md`.

---

## Before launch — user checklist

| Area | What to change |
|------|----------------|
| Brand & SEO | `src/app/layout.tsx` (`metadata.title`, `description`), `package.json` `name` |
| Favicon & icons | See **Favicon** below |
| Copy | `src/content/landing.ts`, auth forms, `src/messages/*.json` |
| Theme | `--app-*` tokens in `src/app/globals.css`; **pick a font first** — `src/config/fonts.ts` + `layout.tsx` + `--app-font` (see `docs/FONTS.md`) |
| Env | `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`, deployment env on platform + **template-services** |
| Routes | Remove or replace placeholder footer links (`#` privacy/terms) |

---

## Favicon (user must replace)

Use the product favicon before shipping. Next.js App Router picks up files under **`src/app/`**:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| **`src/app/favicon.ico`** | Browser tab icon (required baseline) |
| `src/app/icon.png` | Optional PNG app icon |
| `src/app/apple-icon.png` | Optional Apple touch icon |

Alternatively, place assets in **`public/`** (e.g. `public/favicon.ico`) and declare them in **`src/app/layout.tsx`** via `metadata.icons`.

Remove or replace legacy template assets in `public/` (e.g. `chain_16.png`, `chain_64.png`) when rebranding.

---

## i18n — two languages by default

- **Default locales**: `en` and `es`.
- **Message bundles**: `src/messages/en.json`, `src/messages/es.json` — keep keys in sync across files.
- **Client hook**: `src/i18n/client.ts` (`useMessages`, `readLocaleFromCookie`).
- **Locale routing**: `src/proxy.ts` strips `/en` and `/es` prefixes and sets the `NEXT_LOCALE` cookie.

**Adding a third language (e.g. `fr`):**

1. Add `src/messages/fr.json` with the same key structure as `en.json`.
2. Extend `Locale` type and bundles in `src/i18n/client.ts`.
3. Update `src/proxy.ts` matcher/prefix handling if URL prefixes are used.
4. Wire new copy in components (auth forms, dashboard, landing if localized).

Landing copy currently lives in **`src/content/landing.ts`** (English only). Move strings to message bundles when localizing the marketing page.

